author: Val Brickates Kennedy
title: Organogenesis stock jumps 17% on Q4 report, outlook
text:
Organogenesis (NASDAQ:ORGO) stock rallied 17% post-market on Thursday after the company released a Q4 earnings report and guidance that topped Street expectations.
The biotech company reported a Q4 net profit of $0.04 per share on revenue of $127M. Analysts, on average, were expecting a net loss of $0.02 per share on revenue of $110M.
Looking ahead, Organogenesis (NASDAQ:ORGO) is expecting 2025 net revenue in the range of $480M and $535M. Analysts, on average, were expecting revenue of $473M.
